003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224383918\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022224485\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221714571618\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022193460\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Flush Foot\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n13 minutes ago, Flush Foot said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs much as I disagree with much of what NexusHopium says, when I checked Dakota\u0027s LinkedIn page (on mobile, anyways), I also did not see that \u0027#OpenForWork\u0027 banner / flag that was circulating overnight\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca data-fileid=\u0022undefined\u0022 href=\u0022https://preview.redd.it/dakota-is-listed-as-open-to-work-on-linkedin-v0-h0c7t54gvqxc1.jpeg?auto=webp\u0026amp;s=877df4d486d86ef0ee035ba006169597fece4630\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022dakota-is-listed-as-open-to-work-on-link\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u002266.27\u0022 height=\u0022662\u0022 width=\u0022999\u0022 src=\u0022https://preview.redd.it/dakota-is-listed-as-open-to-work-on-linkedin-v0-h0c7t54gvqxc1.jpeg?auto=webp\u0026amp;s=877df4d486d86ef0ee035ba006169597fece4630\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEdit: added photo from Reddit, but again, I\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003Edo not\u003C/strong\u003E see that myself...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224383928\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022224485\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221714572315\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002285181\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Yakuzi\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, Yakuzi said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow so?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Icegrx","CreatedById":232176,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-05-01T14:11:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso saw rumors elsewhere that steam reviews were turned off for KSP2\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthis is also false\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"moeggz","CreatedById":107035,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-05-01T14:12:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut the truths are that take two is shutting down an office is Seattle with approximately the same number of people as intercept games. And that they preannounced the cuts would hit private division, and the only known studio in Seattle for private division is IG. This is the first time closure rumors haven\u2019t been immediately squashed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"LameLefty","CreatedById":57336,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-05-01T14:13:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust so you all know, LinkedIn now has all kinds of tiers and nuances to its memberships. Not all profile information is necessarily available by default to free members, or members who don\u2019t pay for the right tier of membership. So just because you and I don\u2019t see anything about Dakota being open to work doesn\u2019t mean he isn\u2019t listing that availability to professional recruiter accounts.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Yakuzi","CreatedById":85181,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-05-01T14:22:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224383916\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022224485\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221714571471\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022230359\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022NexusHelium\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n30 minutes ago, NexusHelium said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.linkedin.com/in/dakotacx/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.linkedin.com/in/dakotacx/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDo you see anywhere \u0022Looking for work\u0022?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRight, everyone knows that social media profiles are immutable right up to the heat death of the universe...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDid you bother to check 9 hours earlier?\u003Cbr\u003E\nPeople change their profile status, who knew. If only there was a way to capture their previous status...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DoomsdayDuck555","CreatedById":229813,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-05-01T14:23:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224383934\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022224485\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221714572767\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022107035\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022moeggz\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 minutes ago, moeggz said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is the first time closure rumors haven\u2019t been immediately squashed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt isn\u2019t work hours yet though\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"pk9sp","CreatedById":229508,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-05-01T14:27:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.eurogamer.net/kerbal-space-program-2-studio-reportedly-shut-down-by-take-two\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.eurogamer.net/kerbal-space-program-2-studio-reportedly-shut-down-by-take-two\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nan article just hit eurogamer\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:(\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_sad.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:(\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"TLTay","CreatedById":184633,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-05-01T14:27:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224383932\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022224485\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221714572661\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022232176\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Icegrx\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n15 minutes ago, Icegrx said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso saw rumors elsewhere that steam reviews were turned off for KSP2\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthis is also false\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat they said was you cannot make a NEW review right now, not that you couldn\u0027t see reviews or edit existing ones.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Icegrx","CreatedById":232176,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-05-01T14:28:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224383948\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022224485\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221714573661\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022184633\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022TLTay\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, TLTay said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat they said was you cannot make a NEW review right now, not that you couldn\u0027t see reviews or edit existing ones.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, that\u2019s false. You can still make NEW reviews\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"EndeavourCmdr","CreatedById":64194,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-05-01T14:29:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224383948\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022224485\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221714573661\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022184633\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022TLTay\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, TLTay said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat they said was you cannot make a NEW review right now, not that you couldn\u0027t see reviews or edit existing ones.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey do this whenever the algorithm detects unusual review activity. Nothing new there. People freak out and try to \u0022review bomb\u0022, and the algorithm kicks in and makes everyone cool their jets for a bit\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"TLTay","CreatedById":184633,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-05-01T14:34:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224383949\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022224485\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221714573700\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022232176\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Icegrx\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, Icegrx said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, that\u2019s false. You can still make NEW reviews\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou verified this personally by making a first review when you\u0027ve never reviewed KSP2 before?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf so, they may be actively managing this as word gets out to try to manage perceptions. It doesn\u0027t necessarily imply ill intent on the part of the one who originally posted, and may vary by jurisdiction based on laws that T2 expects may apply in event of a cancellation.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs for the news, it\u0027s hard to argue with the WARN act legal notice. The team is being laid off. They will not likely hire a new team AGAIN to work on a flailingly failing project.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe only question now is how the existing product is handled and whether purchasers will \u0022get to keep the product they paid for,\u0022\u00A0 get a refund, a 1.0 patch gets pushed out at the last minute, or T2 continues to \u0022work on\u0022 the game until the heat death of the universe.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Icegrx","CreatedById":232176,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-05-01T14:38:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224383952\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022224485\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221714574094\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022184633\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022TLTay\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, TLTay said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou verified this personally by making a first review when you\u0027ve never reviewed KSP2 before?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"TLTay","CreatedById":184633,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-05-01T14:41:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224383954\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022224485\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221714574307\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022232176\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Icegrx\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, Icegrx said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nProbably the review-bombing prevention algorithm kicked in then and has since released it\u0027s grip.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Yakuzi","CreatedById":85181,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-05-01T14:43:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTake Two commented on the recent developments to Game Developer:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0022\u003Cspan\u003ETake-Two confirms Kerbal Space Program 2 is safe despite Seattle layoffs\u0022 - \u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.gamedeveloper.com/business/take-two-confirms-kerbal-space-program-2-is-safe-despite-seattle-layoffs#close-modaln\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Esource\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESeems like not all is lost (maybe). At the very least they\u0027ve stepped up the communication cadence.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222024-05-01T14:45:56Z\u0022 title=\u002205/01/2024 02:45  PM\u0022 data-short=\u0022May 1\u0022\u003EMay 1\u003C/time\u003E by Yakuzi\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Flush Foot","CreatedById":193460,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-05-01T14:47:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224383959\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022224485\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221714574638\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002285181\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Yakuzi\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, Yakuzi said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTake Two commented on the recent developments to Game Developer:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0022\u003Cspan\u003ETake-Two confirms Kerbal Space Program 2 is safe despite Seattle layoffs\u0022 - \u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.gamedeveloper.com/business/take-two-confirms-kerbal-space-program-2-is-safe-despite-seattle-layoffs#close-modaln\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Esource\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 style=\u0022border-width:0px 0px 0px 4px;color:#c9c5be;font-size:15px;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022193460\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed5809095332\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/topic/214646-kerbal-space-program-2-version-10-and-030-hype-train/?do=embed\u0026amp;comment=4383943\u0026amp;embedComment=4383943\u0026amp;embedDo=findComment\u0022 style=\u0022height:217px;max-width:500px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kerbart","CreatedById":78303,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-05-01T14:48:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI hope the staff will get a chance to say their goodbyes but knowing how in general American corporations operate I assume everyone has been cut off from all systems right away.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA lot of us weren\u2019t happy with the product but hoped to see it turn around one day. That day will now never come.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"NexusHelium","CreatedById":230359,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-05-01T14:48:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224383939\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022224485\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221714573322\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002285181\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Yakuzi\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n25 minutes ago, Yakuzi said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDid you bother to check 9 hours earlier?\u003Cbr\u003E\nPeople change their profile status, who knew. If only there was a way to capture their previous status...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFirst of all. Did you see that thing that said they were working at intercept from January 2023 to present.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSecond: Why ask the question if you don\u0027t want to take the facts laid out. The image shown on reddit is extremely old\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224383959\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022224485\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221714574638\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002285181\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Yakuzi\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 minutes ago, Yakuzi said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTake Two commented on the recent developments to Game Developer:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0022\u003Cspan\u003ETake-Two confirms Kerbal Space Program 2 is safe despite Seattle layoffs\u0022 \u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCool cool \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"EndeavourCmdr","CreatedById":64194,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-05-01T14:51:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224383963\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022224485\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221714574924\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002278303\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Kerbart\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, Kerbart said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI hope the staff will get a chance to say their goodbyes but knowing how in general American corporations operate I assume everyone has been cut off from all systems right away.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s not how that works. Here, companies of more than 100 employees are required to give 60 days notice when a major layoff happens.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DeadJohn","CreatedById":201293,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-05-01T14:53:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224383959\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022224485\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221714574638\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002285181\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Yakuzi\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n22 minutes ago, Yakuzi said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTake Two commented on the recent developments to Game Developer:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0022\u003Cspan\u003ETake-Two confirms Kerbal Space Program 2 is safe despite Seattle layoffs\u0022 - \u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.gamedeveloper.com/business/take-two-confirms-kerbal-space-program-2-is-safe-despite-seattle-layoffs#close-modaln\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Esource\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks for the info.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nReading the text within that article doesn\u0027t quite say KSP2 is safe, despite the headline. The article says KSP2 will continue to get \u0022support\u0022 but doesn\u0027t actually promise ongoing development. Support could be as small as one part-time staffer answering emails from EA customers. T2 is quoted making legalese and no-comment statements in that article.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaybe KSP2 is safe. Maybe it\u0027s not. The only thing that seems clear from the article is T2 has an attorney overseeing their statements.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222024-05-01T15:07:45Z\u0022 title=\u002205/01/2024 03:07  PM\u0022 data-short=\u0022May 1\u0022\u003EMay 1\u003C/time\u003E by DeadJohn\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003Egrammar\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}